The article reports on remarks made by Georgian Prime Minister Kvirikashvili and US Vice President Pence during a press conference in Georgia. They discussed the strong partnership between the two countries, Georgia's progress in democratic development and its aspirations for NATO membership, and the challenges posed by Russian aggression. Pence reaffirmed the US commitment to Georgia's territorial integrity and praised Georgia's contribution to international security efforts. He also mentioned the signing of new sanctions against Russia by President Trump. Kvirikashvili expressed gratitude for US support and discussed Georgia's dedication to peaceful resolution of conflicts and economic development.